It helps to draw a diagram using the supplied mean (\(\mu=59\)) and standard deviation (\(\sigma=9\)).





  1. The answer is 0.5 because \(\text{prop}[X<59]=0.5\).



  2. The answer is 0.84 because \(\text{prop}[X>50]=0.84\).



  3. The answer is 0.96 because \(\text{prop}[|X-59|<18]=0.96\).



  4. The answer is 77 because \(\text{prop}[X<77]=0.98\).



  5. The answer is 41 because \(\text{prop}[X>41]=0.98\).



  6. The answer is 9 because \(\text{prop}[|X-59|<9]=0.68\).
